# @kit/brain-monitor

> ðŸ§  Monorepo validation orchestrator with real-time log monitoring

## Overview

`@kit/brain-monitor` is a development utility that centralizes validation tasks and log monitoring for monorepo projects. It automatically detects available test suites, runs validations in parallel, and generates shared task-list markdown files that multiple AI agents can consume without conflicts.

## Features

- **ðŸ” Auto-detection**: Discovers test suites across your monorepo
- **ðŸ“Š Unified reporting**: Generates markdown task lists in `_errors/`
- **ðŸ“ Real-time logging**: Streams dev server logs to `_logs/`
- **âš¡ Parallel execution**: Runs multiple validations concurrently
- **ðŸ‘ï¸ Watch mode**: Continuous validation with file watching
- **ðŸ¤– AI-friendly**: Designed for multi-agent collaboration
- **ðŸš€ Zero-config**: Works out of the box with standard monorepo patterns
- **ðŸŽ¯ CI/CD Integration**: Generates GitHub Actions workflows with PR comments
- **ðŸ§ª Local CI Testing**: Test workflows locally with act before pushing
- **ðŸŽ¨ Cursor IDE support**: Auto-installs validation rules for AI assistants
- **ðŸŒ Browser Console Capture**: Automatically captures browser console logs to files
- **ðŸ”§ Dynamic Package Discovery**: Automatically finds all packages with dev scripts
- **ðŸ”„ Seamless Dev Integration**: Enhances your existing 'pnpm dev' workflow

## Installation

```bash
# Install in your monorepo
pnpm add -D @kit/brain-monitor

# Initialize (adds scripts and documentation)
pnpm brain-monitor init

# Your regular 'pnpm dev' now includes automatic logging!
```

## Usage

### CLI Commands

```bash
# Run all validations (typecheck, lint, format, tests)
brain-monitor validate

# Watch mode for continuous validation
brain-monitor watch         # TypeScript + Lint only (fast)
brain-monitor watch --all   # All validations including tests

